I"TH<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
<p><strong><a href="https://gcc.gnu.org/">GCC</a></strong> is the most widely used and reliable compiler in the world. Several of the world’s most widely used software were (and are) compiled by him.</p>

<p>However, developers are driven by novelty and somehow speculation. And many have heard of <strong><a href="https://llvm.org/">LLVM</a></strong> and most of the time have gotten good information. This way, many have been using it, but are still afraid about 3 essential requirements:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Security</strong>;</li>
  <li><strong>Speed ​​</strong>;</li>
  <li>and <strong>Reliability</strong>.</li>
</ul>

<p>We’ll look at benchmarking information and testing in this article and come to a conclusion.</p>

