<h2 id="compiling-with-gcc">Compiling with GCC:</h2>
<h3 id="c-language">C language:</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Single file:</li>
</ul>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">gcc main.c <span class="nt">-o</span> binary</code></pre></figure>

<ul>
  <li>Multiple Files:</li>
</ul>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">gcc main.c other.c <span class="nt">-o</span> binary</code></pre></figure>

<blockquote>
  <p>You can exchange the <code class="highlighter-rouge">gcc</code> command for only<code class="highlighter-rouge"> cc</code> which is a symbolic link to it:</p>
</blockquote>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">which cc
<span class="c"># /usr/bin/cc</span>
<span class="nb">ls</span> <span class="nt">-l</span> /usr/bin/cc
<span class="c">## lrwxrwxrwx 1 root 42 Nov 23 19:41 /usr/bin/cc -&gt; /usr/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/gcc-bin/9.2.0/gcc</span></code></pre></figure>

